This paper discusses data mining techniques in automated and interactive theorem proving, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of statistical methods for pattern recognition also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of interactive theorem proving, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the use of big data and machine learning techniques suggests a connection to deep learning (cs.DL).
